Architecture plan for Issues #103 and #104

Project structure and module organization:
- Next.js App Router frontend lives under `src/app`; the admin page is `src/app/(admin)/admin/page.tsx` and public subspace detail pages are under `src/app/(public)/s/[slug]/page.tsx`.
- Shared client UI components live under `src/components`. Existing `SubspaceAdminPanel` and `PostEditorPanel` establish the admin form/list pattern; a new `TagAdminPanel` should live beside them in `src/components/tag-admin-panel.tsx`.
- Shared admin API types and client helpers live in `src/lib/admin-api.ts`. Add tag input/action/delete result types and `createTag`, `updateTag`, and `deleteTag` helpers there so the tag panel follows the existing subspace/post API style.
- Prisma access for server-rendered public pages already uses `src/lib/db.ts`; issue #104 should keep the subspace post query local to the subspace page unless repeated post-card logic emerges.
- Rust Axum API modules live in `src-rs`. The tag endpoints already exist in `src-rs/tags.rs`, so issue #103 is primarily frontend wiring rather than backend API work.

Dependencies between issues:
- Issues #103 and #104 are independent and can be implemented in either order.
- #103 depends on the existing Axum tag endpoints and the existing admin page's `tags` data fetch.
- #104 depends on Prisma's existing `Subspace -> Post -> User/Tag` relations and the post detail route `/s/[slug]/[postId]`.
- There is no shared schema migration required for either issue.

Key design decisions:
- Keep the admin tag UI consistent with `SubspaceAdminPanel`: local optimistic state, selectable existing records, create/edit form, explicit delete confirmation, sorted list, and field-level error display.
- Reuse `SerializedTag` from `src/lib/admin-api.ts` for the tag panel and post editor; if tag admin mutates tag data, state remains local to the panel for this issue rather than trying to live-update `PostEditorPanel` tag choices across sibling components.
- Keep tag delete behavior explicit and destructive, relying on backend constraints/cascade behavior already defined for `post_tags`.
- For #104, extend `getSubspace()` to include posts with author and tags ordered newest-first, then render actual linked post cards. Preserve the empty state only when the query returns zero posts.
- Remove the subspace Created/Updated metadata cards entirely and simplify the section heading by avoiding the redundant `Posts in {subspace.name}` wording.
- Use existing title/excerpt/date formatting patterns from the homepage/post detail pages rather than introducing new dependencies.
- Verification should include TypeScript/lint checks and targeted tests where available; no new platform integrations or environment variables are expected.
